{% doc %}
  @prompt
    Create a custom section titled “The Science of Customized Energy” with a deep dusky/indigo blue background (similar to a rich twilight indigo). The typography should match the hero section: bold, modern headings, clean body text, and clear spacing.
    This section has five benefit cards, each with an icon, an eyebrow label, a headline, and a subhead. Cards should have a soft white or very light indigo tint as the background so they pop against the deep indigo section. Add a subtle shadow and rounded corners. Icons should be circular or rounded-square, clean and modern — use simple emoji-style placeholders that are white.
    Spacing should be generous: about 70–80px top/bottom padding for the whole section and 24–32px padding inside each card. Layout should be two columns on desktop, one column on mobile.
    At the bottom of the entire section, centered, include a CTA button styled exactly like my hero button:
    * Black background (#000)
    * White text
    * Medium weight font
    * Rounded corners (6px)
    * Label: “Take the Energy Quiz”
    * Link to: /pages/energy-quiz
    Here is the copy for each segment. Please use these headings exactly:
    
    Page Title: The Science of Customized Energy
    
    Segment 1
    Segment Headline: Engineered for Fast Absorption Headline: Feel It in as little as 5 minutes Subhead: CLIME’s gel format bypasses the slow digestive process. Active ingredients absorb through the mouth and upper GI for fast, smooth onset without the sugar rush or crash. Icon: Stopwatch showing 5 minutes
    
    Segment 2
    Segment Headline: Nature-Derived, Clinically Supported Headline: Mushrooms, Botanicals, and Modern Science Subhead: CLIME combines adaptogens, nootropics, and clean caffeine in ratios that enhance focus and endurance — while balancing stress response. The result: calm energy that lasts. Icon: Mushroom
    
    Segment 3
    Segment Headline: Proven Ingredients, Transparent Science Headline: Real Studies. Real Results. Subhead: Every active ingredient in CLIME traces back to published human data. Explore , There is no copy in two of the cards. There is too much room in the cards. Make the icons line drawings and the shading inside the cards a little more light gray so the contrast isn't too high. Instead of 5 cards, let's just have 4: Engineered for fast absorption; Nature-derived...; Proven ingredients...' and Built for how... Let's get rid of Synergy
{% enddoc %}
{% assign ai_gen_id = block.id | replace: '_', '' | downcase %}

{% style %}
  .ai-science-section-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    background-color: {{ block.settings.background_color }};
    padding: {{ block.settings.section_padding_top }}px 20px {{ block.settings.section_padding_bottom }}px;
  }

  .ai-science-container-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .ai-science-title-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    color: {{ block.settings.title_color }};
    text-align: center;
    font-size: {{ block.settings.title_size }}px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 {{ block.settings.title_margin_bottom }}px;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .ai-science-cards-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: {{ block.settings.card_gap }}px;
    margin-bottom: {{ block.settings.cta_margin_top }}px;
  }

  @media screen and (min-width: 750px) {
    .ai-science-cards-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .ai-science-card-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    background-color: {{ block.settings.card_background }};
    border-radius: {{ block.settings.card_border_radius }}px;
    padding: {{ block.settings.card_padding }}px;
    box-shadow: {{ block.settings.card_shadow_horizontal }}px {{ block.settings.card_shadow_vertical }}px {{ block.settings.card_shadow_blur }}px rgba(0, 0, 0, {{ block.settings.card_shadow_opacity }});
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .ai-science-icon-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    width: {{ block.settings.icon_size }}px;
    height: {{ block.settings.icon_size }}px;
    background-color: {{ block.settings.icon_background }};
    border-radius: {{ block.settings.icon_border_radius }}px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .ai-science-icon-{{ ai_gen_id }} svg {
    width: {{ block.settings.icon_svg_size }}px;
    height: {{ block.settings.icon_svg_size }}px;
    stroke: {{ block.settings.icon_color }};
    fill: none;
    stroke-width: 2;
    stroke-linecap: round;
    stroke-linejoin: round;
  }

  .ai-science-eyebrow-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    color: {{ block.settings.eyebrow_color }};
    font-size: {{ block.settings.eyebrow_size }}px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .ai-science-headline-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    color: {{ block.settings.headline_color }};
    font-size: {{ block.settings.headline_size }}px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .ai-science-subhead-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    color: {{ block.settings.subhead_color }};
    font-size: {{ block.settings.subhead_size }}px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .ai-science-cta-wrapper-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .ai-science-cta-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    display: inline-block;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
    color: {{ block.settings.cta_text_color }};
    padding: {{ block.settings.cta_padding_vertical }}px {{ block.settings.cta_padding_horizontal }}px;
    border-radius: {{ block.settings.cta_border_radius }}px;
    font-size: {{ block.settings.cta_font_size }}px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1.5px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .ai-science-cta-{{ ai_gen_id }}:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
    border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
  }

  .ai-science-cta-{{ ai_gen_id }}:active {
    transform: translateY(0);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  }
{% endstyle %}

